The paper deals with graph parameters and their complexity, which suggests that it belongs to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The focus on kernelization and structural parameters also suggests Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG) as likely categories. The use of graph reduction rules and analysis of success rates suggests Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) as a possible category. Finally, the study of pathwidth and related parameters suggests Graph Theory (cs.GT) as another likely category.
